{"title_page": "Acidisoma", "text_new": "{{Italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = ''Acidisoma''\n| domain = [[Bacteria]]\n| phylum = \"[[Proteobacteria]]\"\n| classis = [[Alphaproteobacteria]]\n| ordo = [[Rhodospirillales]]\n| familia = [[Acetobacteraceae]]\n| genus = ''Acidisoma''\n| binomial_authority =  Belova ''et al''. 2009<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.009209-0 | volume=59 | title=Acidisoma tundrae gen. nov., sp. nov. and Acidisoma sibiricum sp. nov., two acidophilic, psychrotolerant members of the Alphaproteobacteria from acidic northern wetlands | year=2009 | journal=International Journal of Systematic and Evolutionary Microbiology | pages=2283\u20132290 | last1 = Belova | first1 = S. E.| doi-access=free }}</ref>\n| type_species = A. tundrae \n| subdivision_ranks = Species \n}}\n\n'''''Acidisoma''''' is a genus in the phylum [[Proteobacteria]] ([[Bacteria]]). It contains two species, ''[[Acidisoma tundrae]]'' and ''[[Acidisoma sibiricum]]'', both  two acidophilic (pH 3.0\u20137.6) and psychrotolerant (2\u201330&nbsp;\u00b0C) bacteria with [[poly-\u03b2-hydroxybutyrate]] granules, isolated from acidic [[Sphagnum]]-dominated tundra and Siberian wetlands in Russia.<ref>{{cite journal | last1 = Belova | first1 = S.E. | last2 = Pankratov | first2 = T.A. | last3 = Detkova | first3 = E.N. | last4 = Kaparullina | first4 = E.N. | last5 = Dedysh | first5 = S.N. | year = 2009 | title = Acidisoma tundrae gen. nov., sp. nov. and Acidisoma sibiricum sp. nov., two acidophilic, psychrotolerant members of the Alphaproteobacteria from acidic northern wetlands | url = | journal = Int. J. Syst. Evol. Microbiol | volume = 59 | issue = | pages = 2283\u20132290 }}</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\nThe name ''Acidisoma'' derives from:<br/>[[New Latin]] noun ''acidum'' (from [[Latin]] adjective ''acidus'' -''a'' -''um'', sour, tart, acid), an acid; [[Ancient Greek language|Greek]] [[grammatical gender|neuter gender]] noun ''soma (\u03c3\u1ff6\u03bc\u03b1)'', body; [[New Latin]] [[grammatical gender|neuter gender]] noun ''Acidisoma'', an acid (-requiring) body.<ref name=main>{{lpsn|a/acidisoma.html|Acidisoma}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bacterial taxonomy]]\n* [[Microbiology]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q4674103}}\n\n[[Category:Bacteria genera]]\n[[Category:Rhodospirillales]]\n", "text_old": "{{Italic title}}\n{{Taxobox\n| name = ''Acidisoma''\n| domain = [[Bacteria]]\n| phylum = \"[[Proteobacteria]]\"\n| classis = [[Alphaproteobacteria]]\n| ordo = [[Rhodospirillales]]\n| familia = [[Acetobacteraceae]]\n| genus = ''Acidisoma''\n| binomial_authority =  Belova ''et al''. 2009<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1099/ijs.0.009209-0 | volume=59 | title=Acidisoma tundrae gen. nov., sp. nov. and Acidisoma sibiricum sp. nov., two acidophilic, psychrotolerant members of the Alphaproteobacteria from acidic northern wetlands | year=2009 | journal=INTERNATIONAL JOURNAL OF SYSTEMATIC AND EVOLUTIONARY MICROBIOLOGY | pages=2283\u20132290 | last1 = Belova | first1 = S. E.| doi-access=free }}</ref>\n| type_species = A. tundrae \n| subdivision_ranks = Species \n}}\n\n'''''Acidisoma''''' is a genus in the phylum [[Proteobacteria]] ([[Bacteria]]). It contains two species, ''[[Acidisoma tundrae]]'' and ''[[Acidisoma sibiricum]]'', both  two acidophilic (pH 3.0\u20137.6) and psychrotolerant (2\u201330&nbsp;\u00b0C) bacteria with [[poly-\u03b2-hydroxybutyrate]] granules, isolated from acidic [[Sphagnum]]-dominated tundra and Siberian wetlands in Russia.<ref>BELOVA (S.E.), PANKRATOV (T.A.), DETKOVA (E.N.), KAPARULLINA (E.N.) and DEDYSH (S.N.): Acidisoma tundrae gen. nov., sp. nov. and Acidisoma sibiricum sp. nov., two acidophilic, psychrotolerant members of the Alphaproteobacteria from acidic northern wetlands. Int. J. Syst. Evol. Microbiol., 2009, 59, 2283-2290.</ref>\n\n==Etymology==\nThe name ''Acidisoma'' derives from:<br/>[[New Latin]] noun ''acidum'' (from [[Latin]] adjective ''acidus'' -''a'' -''um'', sour, tart, acid), an acid; [[Ancient Greek language|Greek]] [[grammatical gender|neuter gender]] noun ''soma (\u03c3\u1ff6\u03bc\u03b1)'', body; [[New Latin]] [[grammatical gender|neuter gender]] noun ''Acidisoma'', an acid (-requiring) body.<ref name=main>{{lpsn|a/acidisoma.html|Acidisoma}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Bacterial taxonomy]]\n* [[Microbiology]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q4674103}}\n\n[[Category:Bacteria genera]]\n[[Category:Rhodospirillales]]\n", "name_user": "Rjwilmsi", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Journal cites:,", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acidisoma"}
